description: The xy locations of gun manufacturers and the number of guns. The data is based on ATF (Bureua of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Exlposive) report on gun manufacturers across the U.S. in 2005. The original file is a PDF document, which was converted to a tab-delimted text file and geocoded.  The ATF annual report was prepared in January 2007. The report has 79% of the firearms manufacturers which include production of rifles (1.14 million), revolvers (275k), shot guns (622k) and pistols (815k).
